1:1 COMMENT "# unit_dissect.z -- compile-time dissection of a generic UNIT's type parameter."
1:80 EOL "\n"
2:1 COMMENT "# `match t` inside a `unit as { t: Any.generic }` selects a code path by the"
2:77 EOL "\n"
3:1 COMMENT "# parameter's concrete type at monomorphisation; only the matching arm survives"
3:80 EOL "\n"
4:1 COMMENT "# in the generated C (the zerolang analogue of #ifdef), exactly as in class"
4:76 EOL "\n"
5:1 COMMENT "# methods and free functions. The dissecting method takes no arguments -- the"
5:78 EOL "\n"
6:1 COMMENT "# generic parameter is in scope from the enclosing unit."
6:57 EOL "\n"
7:1 EOL "\n"
